Thank you 😊 

I can’t express how much fulfillment I’ve gained by taking on this journey because of a vision board.

If you told me at the beginning of the year all the things I’ve experienced, I would say you’re lying. But no, exploring the climbing community & making these videos allowed me to make connections with people worldwide & within my city. 

For the friends I’ve made
thank you for taking me under your wing and giving me so much knowledge about the sport. You guys have welcomed me into this community and shown me how loving & supportive it is, so from the bottom of my heart, thank you. Thank you for the fun experiences we’ve shared during our trips to new gyms, the glen, TMU boulders, RRG, and all the psych every session.

For the people worldwide
Thank you for all the love & support. 
I genuinely think I don’t deserve it because I’m just a kid exploring a dream, but I would receive messages from people across the world telling me how my videos inspired them to get into or try climbing. Each person I had a conversation with left an impact on me. One of them being a little kid from Australia that really left an indelible mark on my heart. So because of you, I’m motivated to keep making these videos and encourage others to give this sport a try. 

My goal with the vision board was vague, but at its core it was about trying my hardest in climbing. Looking back now, I think I’ve achieved that. 

So overall, I’m just extremely thankful for the moments & friendships I’ve made with everyone this year.
Whether that be through DM, at events, or simply climbing at the gym together. Thank you for sharing a moment with me💫

Now it’s time for me to explore this vision board even further in 2024.
